President Donald J. Trump and members of Congress are highlighting the benefits of historic tax cuts and reforms for American families and businesses on Tax Day. They emphasize that this is the last year Americans will fill out outdated, complicated tax forms, as future taxes will be completed on a simple, single sheet of paper. They also point out that the new tax code prioritizes middle-class tax relief, higher wages, and job creation. Additionally, they highlight that the tax cuts allow individuals and businesses to keep more of their hard-earned money and invest in the economy. Overall, they believe that the new tax code will lead to economic revival and benefit American families and businesses.